{"serial": "41018", "department_serial": 38, "code": "BA5011", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Seminar on NPO Management", "ch": "非營利組織管理專題"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "何䓝涵老師"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Ho, Meng-Han"], "ch": ["何䓝涵"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "111"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 30, "department": {"ch": "企業管理學系", "en": "Department of Business Administration"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 19, "remark": {"ch": "何䓝涵老師", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程的目標如下。\n1. 讓學生熟悉非營利組織管理研究的核心問題。\n2. 讓學生熟悉非營利組織管理的概念和理論。\n3. 最重要的是，鼓勵學生參與社區活動並批判性地思考其重要性，我們個人和作為非營利組織或其他相關組織的領導者可以採取的行動為何？\n\n總而言之，本課程為學生提供一般非營利組織管理專業課程以外的見解，學生將獲得有關如何運用在現實世界的實作知識。", "en": "The objectives of this course are as follows. \n1. To familiarize students with some core issues and debates within the study of nonprofit management.\n2. To acquaint students with concepts and theories of nonprofit organizations that bear upon the issues and debates.\n3. Most importantly, to encourage students to participate in community engagement and critically think about why that matters. And what can we do about it, individually and as leaders of nonprofit or related organizations?\nOverall, this course provides you with insights that extend beyond the standard curriculum, and you will gain practical knowledge on how to navigate real-world applications."}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程主題包含非營利組織、非營利組織和其他組織的分別、志工服務、服務學習、捐獻、公益慈善、社會企業與創新。學生將學習閱讀英文期刊論文，撰寫參考文獻註釋範例，整理文獻重點，了解非營利組織管理的概念與理論後，再進一步參與非營利組織志工服務，反思志工服務的重要性及思考非營利組織管理的問題。最後學生將和在地非營利組織/社會企業合作，實際探討組織困境與需求，進而提出能夠運用在現實世界中的實作內容。", "en": "The topics of this course include nonprofit organizations, differentiating nonprofit organizations, volunteering, service learning, donations, philanthropy, social enterprises, and innovation. Students will learn to read English journal articles, write a brief annotated bibliography, summarize the key points of literature, and understand the concepts and theories of nonprofit management. After their service learning activities, they will reflect on the importance of volunteering and nonprofit management issues. Finally, students will work with local nonprofit organizations/social enterprises to discuss organizational difficulties and needs, and then propose practical content that can be applied in the real world."}, "textbook": {"ch": "無", "en": "無"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "50", "en": "50"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "50％", "en": "50％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "請先行", "en": "By appointment"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "基礎知識\n\n\n、\n\n\n基礎管理", "en": "基礎知識\n\n\n、\n\n\n基礎管理"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "原創性", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "熟悉其專業領域文獻", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "獨立思考和解決問題能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "溝通能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Original Contribution", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)", "Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Proficiency with Discipline-related Literature", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)", "Attendance/Performance", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Critical Thinking and Problem-solving", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentat